WEBVTT

00:01.860 --> 00:04.192
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]

00:09.570 --> 00:11.606
[ CAMERA SHU'I'I'ER CLICKING ]

00:14.280 --> 00:16.646
HEY.
HEY. OH.

00:16.680 --> 00:17.772
YOU HAD ANYTHING
TO EAT?

00:17.810 --> 00:18.879
THANK YOU.
NO, THANKS.

00:18.910 --> 00:20.309
I'LL GET SOMETHING
IN A MINUTE.

00:22.390 --> 00:24.017
MAN,
I HATE THIS.

00:24.050 --> 00:27.315
WAS REALLY HOPING THAT HE'D BE
ON A BEACH SOMEWHERE.

00:27.360 --> 00:31.251
Sam: EIGHT HOURS AGO,
WE FOUND THE BODY OF BRIAN GOWDY

00:31.290 --> 00:33.429
IN THE TRUNK OF HIS CAR,
BEATEN TO DEATH.

00:33.460 --> 00:35.792
GOWDY WENT MISSING
AFTER TAKING AN UNKNOWN SUBJECT

00:35.830 --> 00:39.095
FOR A TEST-DRIVE
OF GOWDY'S BLACK XJ8.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.233
THE DAY BEFORE GOWDY WAS KILLED,

00:41.270 --> 00:44.831
DR. MILO HOWARD
REPORTED A SUSPICIOUS MAN

00:44.870 --> 00:48.237
WHO SHOWED UP TO TEST-DRIVE
DR. HOWARD'S BLACK XJ8.

00:48.280 --> 00:49.804
ALL RIGHT,
BOTH THESE VEHICLES WERE LISTED

00:49.850 --> 00:53.217
ON THE CAR-SALES WEBSITE
rldeswapper.com,

00:53.250 --> 00:55.571
AND TEXT MESSAGES CONFIRM
THAT IT'S THE SAME BUYER.

00:55.620 --> 00:57.781
OKAY, WE MIGHT BE LOOKING
AT A SERIAL PREDATOR

00:57.820 --> 00:59.981
WHO'S HUNTING HIS VICTIMS
ONLINE.

01:00.020 --> 01:02.454
DR. HOWARD, OUR EYEWITNESS,
DESCRIBES THE MALE SUSPECT

01:02.490 --> 01:07.098
AS CAUCASIAN, MID 30$,
DARK HAIR, TALL, ABOUT 195.

01:07.130 --> 01:10.258
THEY MET AT A GAS STATION
ON LAKE SHORE.

01:10.300 --> 01:12.939
THE SUSPECT SHOWED UP
IN A GRAY SEDAN.

01:12.970 --> 01:15.598
THE NEXT DAY, BRIAN GOWDY,
OUR VICTIM,

01:15.640 --> 01:18.359
MET THE SUSPECT
AT THE SAME GAS STATION.

01:18.410 --> 01:20.275
NOW, WE DON'T HAVE A VISUAL
ON THE KILLER,

01:20.310 --> 01:21.971
BUT WE DO HAVE
SOME SECURITY FOOTAGE

01:22.010 --> 01:25.605
SHOWING A GRAY CRUZE SEDAN
PULLING INTO THE LOT.

01:25.650 --> 01:28.414
PARTIAL PLATE --
ALPHA INDIA BRAVO NOVEMBER.

01:28.450 --> 01:29.587
ALL RIGHT, NOW,
PECK AND COLLINS,

01:29.620 --> 01:32.088
YOU'RE GONNA BE ON THE SEDAN.

01:32.120 --> 01:34.714
AND EPSTEIN AND PRICE,
YOU'LL BE WITH OUR VICTIM, OKAY?

01:34.760 --> 01:36.648
FIND OUT EVERYTHING
THAT YOU CAN. MCNALLY?

01:36.690 --> 01:39.454
ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS FOOTAGE OF THE DECEASED

01:39.500 --> 01:41.388
THAT WAS PULLED FROM AN ATM
AT A GAS STATION.

01:41.430 --> 01:43.728
RIGHT NOW,
THIS IS THE LAST KNOWN SIGHTING

01:43.770 --> 01:44.919
OF BRIAN GOWDY ALIVE.

01:44.970 --> 01:46.562
EXCUSE ME. STAFF?
Oliver: YEAH.

01:46.600 --> 01:49.262
JUST LET ME.

01:58.250 --> 02:00.218
[ SIREN WAILS ]

02:00.250 --> 02:03.219
***

02:07.220 --> 02:10.018
I'M SORRY ABOUT YOUR BROTHER,
MR. GOWDY.

02:10.060 --> 02:11.129
MM. YOU WERE CLOSE?

02:11.160 --> 02:13.458
YEAH,
WE WERE VERY CLOSE, AND...

02:13.500 --> 02:16.924
YOU KNOW, TWINS OFTEN, UH, GROW
APART AS THEY GET OLDER,

02:16.970 --> 02:18.369
BUT WE -- WE DIDN'T.

02:18.400 --> 02:20.698
WE WERE --
WE WERE BEST FRIENDS.

02:20.740 --> 02:23.231
DID YOU KNOW YOUR BROTHER WAS
PLANNING TO MOVE TO COSTA RICA?

02:23.270 --> 02:27.969
I-I KNOW HE'D B-BEEN THERE
A COUPLE OF TIMES, BUT...

02:28.010 --> 02:31.446
MR. GOWDY, DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHO MIGHT HAVE DONE THIS?

02:31.480 --> 02:32.617
UH, NO, IT --

02:32.650 --> 02:36.108
LOOK, BRIAN WAS THE KINDEST MAN
IN THE WORLD.

02:36.150 --> 02:38.118
I HAVE NO IDEA WHO WOULD WANT
TO DO THIS TO HIM.

02:39.890 --> 02:41.619
DEX, YOU NEED TO PICK LEO UP
AT 4:00

02:41.660 --> 02:43.958
OR I NEED TO CALL STELLA,
SO CAN YOU CALL ME BACK,

02:43.990 --> 02:46.083
LET ME KNOW
YOU GOT THIS MESSAGE?

02:46.130 --> 02:47.324
THAN KS.

02:47.360 --> 02:49.464
DEX DIDN'T EVEN SHOW UP
TO MEDIATION THIS MORNING.

02:49.500 --> 02:50.467
YOU'RE KIDDING.
NO.

02:50.500 --> 02:51.819
WELL, THAT'S GOOD FOR YOU,
ISN'T IT?

02:51.870 --> 02:53.064
YEAH,
YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN THE GUY

02:53.100 --> 02:54.260
SCRIBBLING
ON HIS JUDGING PAD.

02:55.570 --> 02:57.800
THAT DIDN'T SOUND GOOD,
DID IT?

02:57.840 --> 02:59.979
LOOK, YOU DIDN'T WANT
TO FIGHT THIS BATTLE,

03:00.010 --> 03:01.637
BUT YOU STILL NEED
TO WIN IT.

03:01.680 --> 03:03.307
THANK YOU.

03:03.350 --> 03:04.442
WELCOME.

03:04.480 --> 03:06.846
HEY, CHRIS,
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

03:06.880 --> 03:07.972
NO OTHER DIVISIONS

03:08.020 --> 03:09.749
HAVE REPORTED ANY OTHER
SUSPICIOUS TEST-DRIVES,

03:09.790 --> 03:11.746
BODIES IN CARS,
OR ANY OTHER CRIMINAL ACTIVITY

03:11.790 --> 03:13.155
RELATED
TO ONLINE AUTO SITES.

03:13.190 --> 03:14.919
SO UNLESS THE SUSPECT'S
JUST RAMPING UP,

03:14.960 --> 03:16.257
IT'S NOT
A SERIAL PREDATOR.

03:16.290 --> 03:17.848
YEAH,
BUT WHY WAS GOWDY A TARGET?

03:17.890 --> 03:20.654
I DON'T KNOW. SINGLE,
NO PSYCHO EX-GIRLFRIENDS,

03:20.700 --> 03:23.066
WELL-LOVED BY HIS STAFF
AND STUDENTS -- I...

03:23.100 --> 03:25.318
WELL,
KEEP LOOKING.

03:26.770 --> 03:29.409
I'M TELLING YOU, THERE IS
NOTHING TO FIND ON THIS GUY.

03:29.440 --> 03:31.135
OH, COME ON,
EVERYBODY'S HIDING SOMETHING --

03:31.170 --> 03:33.900
PARKING TICKETS,
PRESCRIPTIONS, HUSBANDS.

03:35.140 --> 03:36.573
I WAS BEING HILARIOUS.

03:36.610 --> 03:37.975
YOU'RE STILL MAD
ABOUT WES.

03:38.010 --> 03:39.409
CHLOE,
I MENTIONED THE GUY.

03:39.450 --> 03:41.714
MENTIONED HIM BECAUSE YOU'RE
OBVIOUSLY STILL UPSET ABOUT IT.

03:41.750 --> 03:42.910
IF I DIDN'T MENTION HIM,

03:42.950 --> 03:45.384
THEN I'D BE SUPPRESSING IT,
AND THAT'S NOT HEALTHY.

03:45.420 --> 03:47.251
FINE.
I WON'T MENTION HIM.

03:47.290 --> 03:48.712
YOU FIND
ANYTHING YET?

03:48.760 --> 03:51.228
OUT OF ALL THE SQUEAKY-CLEAN
GUYS WE INVESTIGATED,

03:51.260 --> 03:52.727
THIS GUY
IS THE SQUEAKIEST.

03:52.760 --> 03:53.954
WELL,
WE THINK HE'S TARGETED,

03:54.000 --> 03:56.969
SO HE'S GOT
TO BE HIDING SOMETHING.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.922
I DON'T KNOW.
TAP INTO YOUR DUPLICITOUS SIDE.

03:58.970 --> 04:00.232
HOW DO PEOPLE
HIDE THINGS?

04:02.870 --> 04:05.100
I KNOW YOU'RE SUPPRESSING IT
RIGHT NOW.

04:05.140 --> 04:09.873
WHOA. 150 LICENSE PLATES
BEGINNING WITH "AIBN."

04:12.150 --> 04:14.414
14 OF THOSE PLATES
BELONG TO GRAY SEDANS.

04:14.450 --> 04:16.509
AND I DON'T BELIEVE
IN ONLINE DATING.

04:16.550 --> 04:17.642
OH, IT'S REAL.

04:17.690 --> 04:18.941
AND I THINK I'M THE BEST PERSON
FOR THE JOB

04:18.990 --> 04:21.458
BECAUSE I KNOW YOU
SO INTIMATELY.

04:21.490 --> 04:23.082
GREAT.

04:23.130 --> 04:24.950
I'M GONNA SAY THAT YOU SLEEP
WITH YOUR EYES HALF-CLOSED,

04:24.990 --> 04:25.957
LIKE A DECAYING CORPSE.

04:25.990 --> 04:27.150
BECAUSE I DO.

04:27.200 --> 04:30.419
AND THAT YOU'VE NEVER
LOST A SOCK A DAY IN YOUR LIFE

04:30.470 --> 04:34.258
TO A SORT OF CREEPY DEGREE
BECAUSE YOU ARE A SOCK TRACKER.

04:35.970 --> 04:37.961
GOD, WOMEN ARE
JUST GONNA EAT THIS UP.

04:38.010 --> 04:39.773
HEY, YOU'RE SINGLE NOW.
I CAN MAKE YOU A PROFILE.

04:39.810 --> 04:41.607
TALK ABOUT HOW YOU FLOSS
YOUR TEETH WITH YOUR HAIR.

04:41.640 --> 04:42.607
NOT ANYMORE.

04:42.650 --> 04:43.674
OOH,
I COULD PUT ON THAT VIDEO,

04:43.710 --> 04:44.972
YOU ARGUING
WITH THE PARKING GUY

04:45.010 --> 04:46.671
WITH YOUR MOUTH STILL FROZEN
FROM THE DENTIST.

04:46.720 --> 04:48.415
NO, YOU DON'T HAVE A VIDEO
OF THAT.

04:48.450 --> 04:49.587
[ Slurring ] I WILL ALWAYS
HAVE A VIDEO OF THAT.

04:49.620 --> 04:50.985
GOT ANYTHING?

04:51.020 --> 04:52.009
UH, YES.

04:52.050 --> 04:53.779
WE HAVE
EIGHT GRAY CRUZE SEDANS

04:53.820 --> 04:55.651
WITH PLATES
STARTING WITH "AIBN."

04:55.690 --> 04:58.818
WITNESS SAYS THE SUSPECT IS A
CAUCASIAN, 30$, DARK-BROWN HAIR.

04:58.860 --> 04:59.827
OOH.
YEP.

04:59.860 --> 05:01.350
TRACI,
THAT COULD BE ANY...BODY.

05:02.300 --> 05:04.359
IT COULD BE NICK.

05:04.400 --> 05:06.834
I HAVE AN ALIBI.
NOPE.

05:06.870 --> 05:08.929
NOPE.

05:08.970 --> 05:10.506
WAIT. THERE'S ONE.

05:10.540 --> 05:14.874
SEAN HARRISON, 34 YEARS OLD,
LIVES AT 59 DALMAY STREET.

05:14.910 --> 05:15.899
OKAY.

05:15.940 --> 05:18.204
LET'S SEE
IF HE'LL COME IN FOR A CHAT.

05:18.250 --> 05:19.979
ALL RIGHT.
OKAY.

05:22.520 --> 05:24.511
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

05:32.830 --> 05:35.196
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

05:38.930 --> 05:39.999
SEAN HARRISON.

05:40.040 --> 05:41.462
YEAH.

05:41.500 --> 05:42.535
SOMETHING GOING ON?

05:42.570 --> 05:44.367
CAN YOU LET US IN?
IT'S COLD OUTSIDE.

05:47.410 --> 05:50.345
MR. HARRISON,
WE BELIEVE A GRAY SEDAN
REGISTERED IN YOUR NAME

05:50.380 --> 05:52.610
MAY HAVE BEEN USED
IN THE COMMISSION OF A CRIME.

05:52.650 --> 05:54.049
CRIME?

05:54.080 --> 05:55.616
ARE YOU HERE
BY YOURSELF?

05:55.650 --> 05:57.618
YEAH. UNLESS...

05:57.650 --> 06:00.380
KELLY? KELLY?

06:00.420 --> 06:03.651
I GUESS
SHE'S STILL AT WORK.

06:03.690 --> 06:05.328
WOULD YOU MIND JOINING US
DOWN AT THE STATION?

06:05.360 --> 06:07.328
ARE YOU ARRESTING ME?
NO, NO.

06:07.360 --> 06:08.998
WE JUST WANT TO ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS.

06:09.030 --> 06:10.224
CAN I
AT LEAST GET DRESSED?

06:10.270 --> 06:11.464
YEAH, OF COURSE,
AS LONG AS YOU DON'T MIND

06:11.500 --> 06:13.388
IF OFFICER COLLINS
ESCORTS YOU.

06:13.440 --> 06:15.237
I DON'T DO
THE BOYS ANYMORE.

06:20.640 --> 06:22.676
Sam: MR. HARRISON,
DO YOU EVER BUY GAS

06:22.710 --> 06:24.644
AT A STATION
ON LAKE SHORE?

06:24.680 --> 06:26.045
NOPE.

06:26.080 --> 06:28.571
THAT'S ODD BECAUSE YOUR CAR
WAS SEEN THERE THREE DAYS AGO.

06:28.620 --> 06:30.611
SEEN BY WHO?
A GUY SELLING AN XJ8.

06:30.650 --> 06:31.844
OFFICER MCNALLY,
YOU WANT TO TELL SEAN

06:31.890 --> 06:32.879
WHAT HAPPENED
AFTER THAT?

06:32.920 --> 06:34.956
THE NEXT DAY,
ANOTHER PERSON, BRIAN GOWDY,

06:34.990 --> 06:37.629
ARRANGED TO MEET THE SAME PERSON
AT THE SAME GAS STATION

06:37.660 --> 06:38.888
TO TEST-DRIVE
HIS XJ8.

06:38.930 --> 06:41.023
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO TELL YOU.

06:41.060 --> 06:42.925
IT WASN'T ME.
BRIAN GOWDY.

06:42.970 --> 06:44.323
YOU KNOW HIM?

06:44.370 --> 06:45.598
NEVER HEARD
OF HIM.

06:45.630 --> 06:46.733
WHAT DO YOU DO FOR A LIVING,
MR. HARRISON?

06:46.770 --> 06:48.067
I'M A CONTRACTOR.
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

06:50.140 --> 06:53.507
UH,
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

06:53.540 --> 06:55.076
[ BUZZER ]

06:55.110 --> 06:58.898
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

06:58.950 --> 07:01.475
DR. HOWARD,
THANKS FOR COMING IN.

07:01.520 --> 07:02.839
THAT'S NOT HIM.

07:02.890 --> 07:03.845
ARE YOU SURE?

07:03.890 --> 07:05.414
HE MATCHES
YOUR DESCRIPTION,

07:05.450 --> 07:07.509
AND THE CAR YOU SAW
IS REGISTERED TO HIM.

07:07.560 --> 07:08.811
WELL, I'M SORRY,
DETECTIVE,

07:08.860 --> 07:11.021
BUT THAT'S NOT THE MAN
THAT I TOOK ON A TEST-DRIVE.

07:11.060 --> 07:13.392
OKAY.
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

07:13.430 --> 07:15.159
SEAN'S WIFE IS HERE,
MCNALLY.

07:15.200 --> 07:16.895
DR. HOWARD,
THANKS VERY MUCH.

07:16.930 --> 07:19.535
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET THE REST
OF YOUR STATEMENT.

07:19.570 --> 07:21.231
KELLY HARRISON?

07:21.270 --> 07:22.828
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH SEAN?

07:22.870 --> 07:24.030
I'M DETECTIVE SWAREK.

07:24.070 --> 07:25.537
THIS IS
OFFICER MCNALLY.

07:25.570 --> 07:27.538
UM, WE JUST HAVE
A COUPLE QUESTIONS.

07:27.580 --> 07:28.706
OKAY.

07:28.740 --> 07:30.708
DOES ANYONE ELSE HAVE ACCESS
TO YOUR HUSBAND'S CAR,

07:30.750 --> 07:32.809
ANYBODY THAT FITS
YOUR HUSBAND'S DESCRIPTION?

07:32.850 --> 07:34.010
LARRY.

07:34.050 --> 07:35.472
LARRY?
WHO'S LARRY?

07:35.520 --> 07:37.317
HE DIDN'T TELL YOU
ABOUT LARRY?

07:37.350 --> 07:39.215
NO, HE DIDN'T TELL US
ABOUT LARRY.
MNH-MNH.

07:39.250 --> 07:40.683
THEY'RE BLOOD BROTHERS
OR SOMETHING

07:40.720 --> 07:42.449
'CAUSE THEY GREW UP
IN THE SAME GROUP HOME.

07:42.490 --> 07:44.754
FAR AS I CAN TELL, IT MEANS
THEY WATCH FOOTBALL TOGETHER

07:44.790 --> 07:47.190
AND LARRY STAYS IN OUR BASEMENT
WHENEVER HE'S OUT OF PRISON.

07:47.230 --> 07:48.891
HE'S STAYING
IN YOUR BASEMENT RIGHT NOW,

07:48.930 --> 07:50.261
AND HE JUST
GOT OUT OF PRISON?

07:50.300 --> 07:53.030
YEAH.
MILLBURN PENITENTIARY.

07:53.070 --> 07:55.937
SEAN PROMISED
HE'D CHANGED.

07:56.970 --> 07:58.506
SO,
IF I WAS GETTING RUN DOWN

07:58.540 --> 08:00.508
FOR A CRIME
I DIDN'T KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT

08:00.540 --> 08:02.428
AND I HAD THIS GUY,
LARRY CHISHOLM --

08:02.480 --> 08:04.243
MCNALLY, WOULD YOU READ OUT
THAT SHEET, PLEASE?

08:04.280 --> 08:06.669
1998, MISDEMEANOR ASSAULT,
12 MONTHS.

08:06.720 --> 08:10.019
2001, ASSAULT CAUSING
BODILY HARM, 24 MONTHS.

08:10.050 --> 08:13.110
2004, ASSAULT WITH
A DEADLY WEAPON, FOUR YEARS.

08:13.160 --> 08:14.809
AND SO ON AND SO FORTH, RIGHT?
PRETTY MUCH.

08:14.860 --> 08:16.384
IF I HAD THAT GUY
LIVING IN MY BASEMENT,

08:16.420 --> 08:18.229
I THINK I'D MENTION HIM --
WOULD YOU MENTION HIM?

08:18.260 --> 08:19.557
I WOULD DEFINITELY
MENTION HIM.

08:19.600 --> 08:22.057
I JUST WANTED TO GIVE HIM
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT,

08:22.100 --> 08:23.658
AT LEAST
UNTIL I TALKED TO HIM.

08:23.700 --> 08:25.190
THE GUY'S
LIKE MY BROTHER.

08:25.230 --> 08:27.289
HEY, WE JUST WANT
TO TALK TO HIM.
I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS.

08:27.340 --> 08:29.865
HE HAD A PAROLE APPOINTMENT
THIS MORNING.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.559
WAS HE WITH YOU
THE AFTERNOONS IN QUESTION?

08:31.610 --> 08:35.273
SEAN?

08:35.310 --> 08:37.972
NO. HE WASN'T.

08:38.010 --> 08:40.342
HE SAID HE HAD TO DO SOMETHING.
I DIDN'T ASK WHAT.

08:40.380 --> 08:41.449
WHERE WOULD LARRY BE NOW?

08:41.480 --> 08:43.118
WE'RE GONNA NEED
A LIST OF FAMILY, FRIENDS,

08:43.150 --> 08:44.219
ASSOCIATES, ANYBODY.

08:44.250 --> 08:47.617
[ SIGHS ]
THERE'S NO ONE.

08:47.660 --> 08:48.957
TRUST ME.

08:48.990 --> 08:50.423
IF THERE WERE, HE WOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN STAYING WITH US.

08:50.460 --> 08:51.654
JUST ASK KELLY.

08:51.690 --> 08:53.521
WHAT ABOUT PRISON?
HE'S GOT FRIENDS ON THE INSIDE?

08:53.560 --> 08:55.994
[ SIGHS ]

08:58.170 --> 09:00.559
HE HAD A FIGHT
AWHILE AGO

09:00.600 --> 09:03.865
WITH ANOTHER INMATE,
SO, YEAH, HE...

09:03.910 --> 09:06.606
HAD PEOPLE
WATCHING HIS BACK.

09:06.640 --> 09:08.779
Sam: OUR EYEWITNESS
HAS POSITIVELY IDENTIFIED

09:08.810 --> 09:11.142
LARRY CHISHOLM AS THE MAN
HE TOOK FOR A TEST-DRIVE

09:11.180 --> 09:13.045
THE DAY BEFORE
BRIAN GOWDY WAS KILLED.

09:13.080 --> 09:15.014
Traci: AND IN THE ABSENCE
OF A CONNECTION

09:15.050 --> 09:16.688
BETWEEN THE VICTIM
AND OUR SUSPECT,

09:16.720 --> 09:18.938
OUR WORKING THEORY
IS THAT LARRY WAS DOING A FAVOR

09:18.990 --> 09:20.287
FOR SOMEONE
ON THE INSIDE.

09:20.320 --> 09:21.787
OKAY,
THAT MEANS WE'RE WORKING BOLO,

09:21.820 --> 09:23.788
BORDER CONTROL,
AIRPORTS, CUSTOMS --

09:23.830 --> 09:25.183
Andy: HEY.

09:25.230 --> 09:27.323
SO, LARRY SHOWED UP FOR HIS
PAROLE APPOINTMENT THIS MORNING.

09:27.360 --> 09:28.918
APPARENTLY, HE WAS A WRECK.
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

09:28.960 --> 09:31.121
ALSO, I HAVE THE TECH REPORT
FOR LARRY'S CELL.

09:31.170 --> 09:33.559
UH, WE'VE GOT A TEXT MESSAGE
TO DR. MILO HOWARD,

09:33.600 --> 09:36.239
A TEXT EXCHANGE WITH
BRIAN GOWDY, BUT LISTEN TO THIS.

09:36.270 --> 09:38.807
THREE CALLS TO AN ILLEGAL
CELLPHONE IN MILLBURN PEN

09:38.840 --> 09:40.671
A DAY AFTER
BRIAN GOWDY WAS KILLED.

09:40.710 --> 09:42.075
SO IF HE WAS
REPAYING A DEBT,

09:42.110 --> 09:43.702
THEN HE -- HE MAYBE
CALLED SOMEONE INSIDE

09:43.750 --> 09:45.103
TO LET THEM KNOW
IT WAS DONE.

09:45.150 --> 09:46.401
OKAY,
THANKS VERY MUCH.

09:46.450 --> 09:48.008
THAT WAS THE WARDEN
AT MILLBURN.

09:48.050 --> 09:49.984
HE GAVE US A LIST
OF INMATES LARRY KNEW.

09:50.020 --> 09:51.612
OKAY, NASH, YOU GONNA GO
AND DO THAT?

09:51.650 --> 09:53.186
ACTUALLY, IT'S FINE.
I'LL TAKE IT.

09:53.220 --> 09:54.778
NASH, YOU GOT THIS?
YEAH, I GOT IT.

09:54.820 --> 09:57.880
OKAY, LARRY CHISHOLM
COULD NOT HAVE GOTTEN FAR.

09:57.930 --> 09:59.750
GO AND GET HIM
AND BRING HIM IN.

10:02.330 --> 10:03.763
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

10:03.800 --> 10:05.290
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

10:05.330 --> 10:06.524
HEY.

10:06.570 --> 10:07.559
HEY.

10:07.600 --> 10:10.137
WHAT'RE --
WHAT'RE YOU DOING HERE?

10:10.170 --> 10:12.536
I GOT TRAIL MIX AND TWO COFFEES.
WE'RE GOOD TO GO.

10:12.570 --> 10:14.276
UH...

10:14.310 --> 10:16.676
DON'T YOU THINK
THEY'RE GONNA NEED YOU
FOR INTERVIEWS HERE?

10:16.710 --> 10:18.974
[ SCOFFS ] FORGET IT.
COMING WITH YOU.

10:19.010 --> 10:21.069
I'M GONNA DRIVE.

10:21.120 --> 10:24.146
FINE.
ROAD TRIP. YAY.

10:24.190 --> 10:25.145
YAY.

10:28.220 --> 10:29.585
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10:32.700 --> 10:34.122
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

10:34.160 --> 10:35.923
WHO DID
THE WARDEN GIVE US?

10:35.960 --> 10:39.623
UH, LARRY'S LAUNDRY PARTNER,
SOME GUY HE FOUGHT WITH,

10:39.670 --> 10:43.208
HIS SPONSOR, AND HIS SUPERVISOR
AT THE CALL CENTER.

10:43.240 --> 10:44.559
SPONSOR'S A GOOD ONE.
YOU KNOW?

10:44.610 --> 10:46.635
PEOPLE USUALLY TELL THEIR
SPONSORS EVERYTHING, RIGHT?

10:46.680 --> 10:48.204
YEAH, YOU KNOW,
THAT'S IN CONFIDENCE.

10:48.240 --> 10:50.401
I THINK IF ANYBODY'S GONNA
TELL US WHAT LARRY WAS UP TO,

10:50.450 --> 10:52.406
IT'S GONNA BE
THE GUY HE FOUGHT WITH.

10:52.450 --> 10:54.008
YEAH, I GUESS.

10:54.050 --> 10:56.416
[ SIREN WAILS ]

10:56.450 --> 10:58.179
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

10:58.220 --> 11:00.188
Y-YEAH,
EVERYTHING'S GREAT.

11:00.220 --> 11:01.881
[ VOLUME INCREASES ]

11:01.920 --> 11:03.228
* ARE YOU GONNA WASTE MY TIME? *

11:03.260 --> 11:04.386
MM.

11:04.430 --> 11:06.159
* ARE YOU GONNA BE MINE? *

11:06.190 --> 11:09.353
MY GOLDFISH HAS MORE ENEMIES
THAN BRIAN GOWDY.

11:09.400 --> 11:11.527
I'M PRETTY SURE
THAT'S EVIDENCE.

11:11.570 --> 11:13.197
YEAH.
GREAT, THANK YOU.

11:13.240 --> 11:14.298
UH, I'LL BE
AT THIS NUMBER.

11:14.340 --> 11:15.693
THEY'RE GONNA CALL US BACK
WITHIN THE HOUR

11:15.740 --> 11:17.059
WITH THE FULL
VEHICLE HISTORY REPORT.

11:17.110 --> 11:18.259
OH,
WITHIN THE HOUR.

11:18.310 --> 11:20.130
OH, TAKE YOUR TIME, GUYS.
NO RUSH.

11:20.180 --> 11:21.909
WE'RE JUST LOOKING
FOR A KILLER.

11:21.940 --> 11:23.009
[ GROANS ]

11:23.050 --> 11:25.302
ARE YOU MAD
ABOUT SIEIJCMETHING?

11:25.350 --> 11:27.511
I JUST WANT
TO BE OUT ON THE STREET,

11:27.550 --> 11:29.780
LOOKING FOR THIS GUY,
DOING SOMETHING,

11:29.820 --> 11:31.879
INSTEAD OF RIDING
THIS DESK AGAIN.

11:31.920 --> 11:33.956
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YES, I AM MAD.

11:33.990 --> 11:35.355
DO YOU WANT
TO KNOW WHY?

11:35.390 --> 11:37.085
I'M MAD AT THE PSYCHO
WHO SHOT ME.

11:37.130 --> 11:38.381
I'M ALSO MAD
AT WES

11:38.430 --> 11:41.558
FOR DECIDING TO LEAVE
THIS BLOOD CLOT IN MY NECK.

11:41.600 --> 11:42.760
[ SIGHS ]

11:42.800 --> 11:44.028
ARE YOU MAD AT ME?

11:44.070 --> 11:47.392
NO,
I AM NOT MAD AT YOU...

11:47.440 --> 11:49.169
BESIDES THE FACT
THAT YOU DIDN'T FIGHT WES AT ALL

11:49.200 --> 11:50.462
AT THE HOSPITAL.

11:50.510 --> 11:52.466
PEOPLE DON'T FIGHT THAT WELL
WHEN THEY'RE CAUGHT OFF GUARD.

11:52.510 --> 11:53.477
THAT'S WHY
AMBUSHES WORK.

11:53.510 --> 11:55.000
WELL,
YOU ASKED ME IF I WAS MAD,

11:55.040 --> 11:57.008
AND I'M FEELING MAD,
WHICH IS WHY I SAID YES.

11:57.050 --> 11:59.848
IT'S ONE THING
TO STAND ME UP,

11:59.880 --> 12:01.211
BUT HE DIDN'T EVEN
PICK UP LEO.

12:01.250 --> 12:02.410
WHAT, HE DIDN'T --
HE DIDN'T CALL YOU?

12:02.450 --> 12:03.542
NO, AND --
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

12:03.590 --> 12:04.545
[ SCOFFS ]
OH, IT'S HIM.

12:04.590 --> 12:06.512
DEX?

12:06.550 --> 12:08.689
WHAT?

12:08.720 --> 12:10.881
WHAT?

12:10.930 --> 12:12.659
I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN DO. OKAY.

12:12.690 --> 12:13.952
OKAY.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.560
UH, APPARENTLY, DEX WAS
IN A BAR FIGHT LAST NIGHT,

12:16.600 --> 12:19.899
AND, UH, THE HOSPITAL'S
SAYING SOMEONE NEEDS TO GO

12:19.940 --> 12:22.568
AND PICK HIM UP.
UH, IS HE OKAY?

12:22.600 --> 12:25.239
I DON'T KNOW, BUT A-AM
I SUPPOSED TO LEAVE
HERE NOW? I DON'T KNOW.

12:25.270 --> 12:27.409
DO YOU WANT TO -- DO YOU WANT ME
TO GET HIM, TRACE?
YES. NO!

12:27.440 --> 12:29.738
WHAT?
WHAT?

12:29.780 --> 12:31.668
THAT WOULD BE WEIRD.
IT'S NOT WEIRD.

12:31.710 --> 12:34.042
HE'S YOUR SON'S FATHER.
YOU'RE RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE OF
THIS HOMICIDE INVESTIGATION.

12:34.080 --> 12:35.012
IT'S FINE.

12:35.050 --> 12:36.312
NO BIG DEAL.

12:36.350 --> 12:37.487
[ BUZZER ]

12:37.520 --> 12:39.511
[ STATIC ]

12:44.330 --> 12:45.285
[ RADIO CLICKS OFF ]

12:45.330 --> 12:47.992
Sam: [ SIGHS ]

12:48.030 --> 12:50.567
HOW ABOUT
WE PLAY 20 QUESTIONS?

12:50.600 --> 12:52.227
BUBBLE GUM
OR THE MOON?

12:52.270 --> 12:53.237
HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?

12:53.270 --> 12:54.532
I DIDN'T EVEN
ASK YOU ANYTHING YET.

12:54.570 --> 12:55.594
YOU ALWAYS DO BUBBLE GUM
AND THE MOON.

12:55.640 --> 12:57.699
I KNOW.
THOSE ARE GOOD ONES.

13:00.040 --> 13:01.439
HMM.

13:05.110 --> 13:06.771
I SPY...

13:06.820 --> 13:09.277
YEAH,
NOT SAFE WHILE DRIVING.

13:09.320 --> 13:11.379
LAME.

13:11.420 --> 13:12.785
WELL, DO YOU WANT ME
TO DRIVE FOR A BIT?

13:12.820 --> 13:13.787
OH, NO, NO,
I'M GOOD.

13:13.820 --> 13:15.708
THANKS.
NO? YOU'RE GOOD. YEAH.

13:15.760 --> 13:18.024
[ SIGHS ]

13:18.060 --> 13:21.120
[ RADIO TURNS ON, STATIC ]

13:22.200 --> 13:23.792
HEY, DEX.

13:23.830 --> 13:26.264
I'M HERE
TO GIVE YOU A RIDE HOME.

13:26.300 --> 13:27.392
WHERE'S TRACE?

13:27.440 --> 13:29.089
MAKING A LIVING.
COME ON. HOP IN.

13:29.140 --> 13:30.209
NO, THAN KS.

13:30.240 --> 13:32.800
HOSPITAL SAID
I HAD TO BE RELEASED TO FAMILY,

13:32.840 --> 13:34.603
NOT MY EX'S
LATEST FLING.

13:34.640 --> 13:36.733
WELL, BAR-FIGHTERS
CAN'T BE CHOOSERS, RIGHT?

13:36.780 --> 13:38.008
WELL, IT WASN'T A BAR FIGHT,
OKAY?

13:38.050 --> 13:39.244
SOME GUY
WANTED MY WALLET.

13:39.280 --> 13:40.645
I DIDN'T WANT
TO GIVE IT TO HIM.

13:40.680 --> 13:42.238
YOU GOT MUGGED?
YEAH. I GOT MUGGED.

13:42.280 --> 13:43.941
AT A BAR.

13:43.990 --> 13:45.480
WELL, DO YOU HAVE
A DESCRIPTION OF THE GUY?

13:45.520 --> 13:48.284
I COULD HELP YOU FILE A REPORT
IF YOU WANT.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

13:48.320 --> 13:50.652
HAPPENED SO FAST,
I DIDN'T REALLY GET
A GOOD LOOK AT THEIR FACES.

13:50.690 --> 13:52.487
OH, SO, WAS -- WAS IT A GUY
OR WAS IT GUYS?

13:52.530 --> 13:54.589
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M NOT
GONNA TALK ABOUT THIS WITH YOU.

13:54.630 --> 13:58.168
DEX...YOU MISSED MEDIATION
'CAUSE YOU GOT INTO A BAR FIGHT,

13:58.200 --> 13:59.394
AND THEN
YOU DIDN'T PICK UP YOUR KID.

13:59.430 --> 14:01.660
LOOK,
JUST BECAUSE I GOT ATTACKED

14:01.700 --> 14:04.828
DOESN'T MEAN THAT TRACI'S
NOT WORKING INSANE HOURS.

14:04.870 --> 14:08.169
LEAVING MY KID WITH A SITTER
WHEN HE COULD BE WITH ME?

14:08.210 --> 14:09.370
YOU TALKING CUSTODY NOW?

14:09.410 --> 14:10.877
NO, I'M TALKING
ABOUT WHAT'S BEST FOR LEO.

14:10.910 --> 14:12.207
YEAH. OKAY.

14:12.250 --> 14:14.912
YOU WANT A RIDE
OR WHAT?

14:14.950 --> 14:16.440
NO, THANKS.
I'LL CALL MY BROTHER.

14:16.480 --> 14:18.641
NEXT TIME, WHY DON'T YOU
CALL YOUR BROTHER FIRST?

14:21.660 --> 14:23.082
AT HIS PAROLE MEETING
TWO BLOCKS FROM HERE,

14:23.130 --> 14:24.552
SO LET'S START
WITH SOME OF THE DIVE BARS

14:24.590 --> 14:26.353
IN THE AREA.

14:26.390 --> 14:28.153
[ LAUGHING ]

14:28.200 --> 14:30.395
THAT'S TERRIBLE.

14:30.430 --> 14:33.297
IT'S FOR YOUR PROFILE.
I'M GOOD.

14:33.340 --> 14:36.138
YOU LOOKING FOR THE SUSPECT?
'CAUSEIII'MUBRIVING.

14:36.170 --> 14:38.035
DO YOU REALLY THINK
LARRY'S YUCKING IT UP

14:38.070 --> 14:39.207
WITH SOME STRIPPER?

14:39.240 --> 14:40.901
NO, I THINK THAT
LARRY'S ON THE RUN, BUT...

14:40.940 --> 14:43.272
I DON'T GET WHY HE DIDN'T RUN
AFTER HE KILLED THE GUY.

14:43.310 --> 14:44.402
BECAUSE HE'S SMART.

14:44.450 --> 14:46.077
HE WENT TO HIS PAROLE
APPOINTMENT THIS MORNING,

14:46.110 --> 14:48.169
SO NO ONE'S GONNA REPORT HIM
MISSING FOR TWO WEEKS.

14:48.220 --> 14:51.542
OKAY, SO, ASSUMING
THAT LARRY'S NOT BRAIN-DEAD,

14:51.590 --> 14:53.353
HE KNOWS HE'D HAVE TO SHOW I.D.
TO BUY A PLANE TICKET.

14:53.390 --> 14:57.178
AND HE'S NOT GONNA GET VERY FAR
IN A STOLEN CAR.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.482
BUS STATION.
BUS STATION.

14:59.530 --> 15:01.521
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

15:01.560 --> 15:03.528
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]
[ SCOFFS ]

15:05.600 --> 15:07.739
SO, MY DAD AND I
USED TO PLAY THIS GAME

15:07.770 --> 15:08.930
EVERY TIME
WE WERE ON A ROAD TRIP

15:08.970 --> 15:10.039
CALLED
"TWO TRUTHS AND A LIE."

15:10.070 --> 15:11.765
ACTUALLY,
IT WAS ONE OF THE ONLY TIMES

15:11.810 --> 15:13.573
THAT WE REALLY
OPENED UP TO EACH OTHER.

15:13.610 --> 15:15.669
OH, YEAH.
MM-HMM.

15:15.710 --> 15:17.905
IT WAS A GOOD GAME.

15:17.950 --> 15:19.941
[ SIGHS ]
YOU WANT TO GO FIRST?

15:19.980 --> 15:21.277
THE TRUTH IS,

15:21.320 --> 15:23.709
I REALLY DON'T WANT TO PLAY
"TWO TRUTHS AND A LIE."

15:23.750 --> 15:24.944
NICE TRY.

15:24.990 --> 15:27.015
AND, ALSO, YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO TELL ME WHAT'S TRUE.

15:27.060 --> 15:28.812
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO SAY
TWO TRUTHS AND ONE LIE,

15:28.860 --> 15:29.918
AND THEN
I HAVE TO GUESS.

15:29.960 --> 15:31.120
OKAY.

15:31.160 --> 15:36.518
I'M A COP, I'M A MAN,
I'M A CHICKEN.

15:36.560 --> 15:37.891
FIRST OF ALL,
DON'T TELL ME THAT

15:37.930 --> 15:39.295
IN THE ORDER OF THE TITLE,
OKAY?

15:39.330 --> 15:40.490
IT'S A DEAD GIVEAWAY.

15:40.540 --> 15:42.235
SECOND, TRY TO MAYBE COME UP
WITH THINGS THAT, UH...

15:42.270 --> 15:43.737
I CAN'T TELL
JUST BY LOOKING AT YOU.

15:43.770 --> 15:45.067
OH,
YOU MEAN SECRETS.

15:45.110 --> 15:47.704
OR MAYBE THINGS THAT
HAVE BEEN BUGGING YOU LATELY.

15:47.740 --> 15:51.403
LIKE IN THE LASR- COUPLE HOURS

15:51.450 --> 15:53.509
YOU KNOW, THINGS YOU MIGHT
JUST WANT TO GET OFF YOUR CHEST.

15:58.450 --> 16:01.089
YOU ARE A CHICKEN.

16:01.120 --> 16:03.884
THAT'S THREE TRUTHS.

16:03.930 --> 16:05.921
[THUNDER RUMBLES ]

16:11.470 --> 16:12.528
[ BUZZER ]

16:12.570 --> 16:14.959
YEP, THIS IS LARRY'S CROWD,
ALL RIGHT.

16:15.000 --> 16:18.561
WE'RE THINKING MAYBE HE
OWED SOMEBODY IN HERE A FAVOR,

16:18.610 --> 16:21.408
SOMETHING HE HAD TO
MAKE GOOD ON ONCE HE GOT OUT.

16:21.440 --> 16:23.044
TH ESE GUYS?

16:23.080 --> 16:25.674
THEY'D SELL OUT THEIR
MOTHERS FOR A SPIT
ROLLIE AND A HAIRCUT.

16:25.710 --> 16:28.873
YOU KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT A RECENT
ALTERCATION WITH AN INMATE?

16:28.920 --> 16:30.808
YEAH,
I PULLED THEM APART MYSELF.

16:30.850 --> 16:33.557
BUT IF YOU REALLY WANT
TO FIND OUT WHAT IT'S OVER,

16:33.590 --> 16:36.388
YOU CAN ASK
THE UNWORTHY OPPONENT HIMSELF...

16:36.420 --> 16:39.480
[ BUZZER ]
REMY LeGRANDE.

16:39.530 --> 16:42.988
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

16:43.030 --> 16:44.895
SEE, LARRY PROMISED ME HIS RADIO
WHEN HE GOT OUT.

16:44.930 --> 16:46.158
I MEAN, HE PROMISED,

16:46.200 --> 16:47.758
SO LONG AS I STAYED AWAY
FROM THE MASHED-POTATO VODKA

16:47.800 --> 16:49.563
THAT BEAN JIMMY MAKES
IN THE BACK OF HIS JOHN.

16:49.600 --> 16:50.862
Andy:
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

16:50.910 --> 16:52.639
I-I DRANK THE VODKA,
HE WOULDN'T GIVE ME THE RADIO,

16:52.670 --> 16:54.604
SO I PUNCHED HIM IN THE FACE --
IT WASN'T PERSONAL.

16:54.640 --> 16:56.938
Sam: DID LARRY
OWE ANYONE ANY FAVORS?

16:56.980 --> 16:59.574
PROTECTION,
DEBTS PAID, DEBTS OWED?

16:59.610 --> 17:03.387
UH, I DON'T KNOW.
DAMIEN, MAYBE?

17:03.420 --> 17:04.682
BUT LARRY'S
A GOD LOVER NOW.

17:04.720 --> 17:06.347
HE KEEPS
HIS SIDE OF THE STREET CLEAN,

17:06.390 --> 17:07.812
DOESN'T GET
INTO YOURS, YOU KNOW.

17:07.860 --> 17:09.157
DID HE
CALL YOU RECENTLY?

17:09.190 --> 17:10.452
NO.
YOU GOT A CELLPHONE?

17:10.490 --> 17:12.481
CELLPHONE'S NOT LEGAL
IN HERE, MAN.

17:12.530 --> 17:14.498
COME ON.
WE'RE NOT THE CELLPHONE POLICE.

17:14.530 --> 17:16.054
WE'RE INVESTIGATING
A MURDER.

17:17.630 --> 17:18.767
LARRY'S DEAD?

17:18.800 --> 17:21.030
BECAUSE HE DID SAY
I COULD HAVE HIS RADIO.

17:21.070 --> 17:23.038
I MEAN,
HE'D WANT ME TO HAVE IT.

17:23.070 --> 17:24.833
HE WAS
A REAL STAND-UP GUY.

17:24.870 --> 17:25.837
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR YOUR TIME.

17:25.870 --> 17:28.577
WHAT ABOUT THE RADIO?
GUYS?

17:28.610 --> 17:29.770
HEY, TRACE,
STILL NO WORD

17:29.810 --> 17:31.471
FROM SWAREK AND MCNALLY
UP AT MILLBURN.

17:31.510 --> 17:32.875
WHAT DO YOU GOT
HAPPENING HERE?

17:32.910 --> 17:33.877
NOT MUCH SO FAR.

17:33.920 --> 17:35.012
THERE'S STILL NO CONNECTION

17:35.050 --> 17:36.574
BETWEEN THE VICTIM
AND THE SUSPECT.

17:36.620 --> 17:38.485
I JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH MOTOR VEHICLES.

17:38.520 --> 17:40.715
GUESS WHO WAS THE PREVIOUS OWNER
OF BRIAN GOWDY'S XJ8?

17:40.760 --> 17:42.113
THE TWIN BROTHER,
JIM GOWDY.

17:42.160 --> 17:44.481
WE'RE THINKING THAT MAYBE
HE WAS THE INTENDED VICTIM.

17:44.530 --> 17:46.327
JIM WORKS IN MORTGAGES --
FORECLOSURES.

17:46.360 --> 17:48.749
HE PROBABLY HAS A LOT MORE
ENEMIES THAN BRIAN EVER DID.

17:48.800 --> 17:49.949
OKAY,
IF THAT'S WHAT'S HAPPENING,

17:50.000 --> 17:51.069
HE'S A SITTING DUCK
OUT THERE.

17:51.100 --> 17:52.761
LARRY CHISHOLM
IS STILL AWOL.

17:52.800 --> 17:55.598
WELL, LET'S GET JIM GOWDY
IN HERE RIGHT AWAY.

17:58.540 --> 17:59.962
LARRY WORKED UNDER ME
AT THE CALL CENTER.

18:00.010 --> 18:01.034
I WAS SORRY
TO SEE HIM GO.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.036
YOU WERE HAPPY
WITH LARRY'S WORK?

18:03.080 --> 18:05.605
MOST GUYS IN HERE PHONE IT IN,
LITERALLY.

18:05.650 --> 18:07.868
"HI.
YOU WANT YOUR CARPET CLEANED?"

18:07.920 --> 18:09.148
"NO, THANK YOU."

18:09.180 --> 18:11.614
"OH, OKAY. BYE."

18:11.650 --> 18:14.778
ENTITLED. THINK THE WORLD
OWES THEM SOMETHING.

18:14.820 --> 18:16.617
LARRY WASN'T LIKE THAT?

18:16.660 --> 18:20.551
LARRY LOVED PRAISE
WITH THE HOPE OF A BEATEN PUPPY.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.420
DID LARRY
OWE ANYBODY ANY FAVORS,

18:22.460 --> 18:24.667
DEBTS HE'D HAVE TO REPAY
ONCE HE GOT OUT?

18:24.700 --> 18:26.099
NO,
THAT WASN'T LARRY.

18:26.130 --> 18:28.598
TRUST ME. I KNOW
WHAT GOES ON AROUND HERE.

18:28.640 --> 18:31.529
WOULD YOU BE SURPRISED
IF LARRY RE-OFFENDED?

18:31.570 --> 18:34.130
YES. AND NO.

18:34.180 --> 18:36.808
"YES" BECAUSE
HE WAS SO DAMN EXCITED

18:36.840 --> 18:38.478
TO GET OUT OF HERE
AND MAKE A LIFE FOR HIMSELF.

18:38.510 --> 18:41.217
THAT RIGHT?
HE ASKED ME TO WRITE
A RECOMMENDATION LETTER.

18:41.250 --> 18:43.548
AND "NO" BECAUSE...?

18:43.590 --> 18:46.286
HE NEVER GOT BACK TO ME TO TELL
ME WHERE TO MAIL THE LETTER.

18:46.320 --> 18:47.958
SO I WONDERED.

18:47.990 --> 18:49.412
THAT'S ALL.

18:52.060 --> 18:53.925
SO, YOU THINK
MY BROTHER WAS KILLED

18:53.960 --> 18:55.791
BECAUSE SOMEONE THOUGHT
HE WAS ME?

18:55.830 --> 18:57.127
Traci:
WE'RE NOT SURE.

18:57.170 --> 18:59.024
WE'RE JUST LOOKING
AT ALL THE POSSIBILITIES.

18:59.070 --> 19:02.631
WHEN DID YOU
GIVE BRIAN THE CAR?

19:02.670 --> 19:05.764
UM...I DON'T KNOW.
FOUR MONTHS AGO.

19:05.810 --> 19:09.769
HE WAS VOLUNTEERING,
BRINGING FOOD TO SHELTERS.

19:09.810 --> 19:12.404
GUY DOESN'T EVEN
HAVE A CAR.

19:12.450 --> 19:15.374
HE WAS DOING IT
ON THE BUS, SO...

19:15.420 --> 19:17.285
THOUGHT IT WOULD HELP.

19:17.320 --> 19:19.345
SO HE WAS WORKING
WITH HOMELESS PEOPLE,

19:19.390 --> 19:21.051
GETTING THEM
OFF THE STREET...

19:21.090 --> 19:22.682
AND I FORECLOSE
ON PEOPLE'S HOUSES

19:22.720 --> 19:24.187
AND PUT THEM
OUT ON THE STREET.

19:24.230 --> 19:26.858
DID YOU FORECLOSE
ON THE HOMES

19:26.890 --> 19:30.189
OF ANY INMATES
AT MILLBURN PENITENTIARY?

19:30.230 --> 19:32.369
PROBABLY, YEAH.

19:32.400 --> 19:33.367
Chris: TRACE.

19:33.400 --> 19:35.288
BOLO JUST CAME THROUGH.

19:35.340 --> 19:37.262
WE GOT A GUY FITTING
THE SUSPECT 'S DESCRIPTION,

19:37.310 --> 19:39.460
JUST BOUGHT A TICKET
AT A BUS STATION IN PORT CREDIT.

19:39.510 --> 19:41.705
DISPATCHER: A|| squads --
we got a report of a man

19:41.740 --> 19:43.105
ﬁumg
Larry Chisholm's description

19:43.140 --> 19:44.471
at the bus station
in Port Credit.

19:44.510 --> 19:46.478
He's waiting for the bus
bound for Niagara Falls

19:46.510 --> 19:48.569
departing in 40 minutes, over.

19:48.620 --> 19:51.339
1519 --
WE'RE IN THE IMMEDIATE AREA.

19:55.620 --> 19:57.679
Nick: 1519 --
I GOT A VISUAL ON THE SUSPECT.

19:57.730 --> 20:01.427
Copy, 1519,
and proceed with caution.

20:01.460 --> 20:03.792
HEY, LARRY CHISHOLM!

20:03.830 --> 20:05.627
IF I TOLD YOU
I WAS AN OLYMPIC DECATHLETE,

20:05.670 --> 20:07.865
WOULD YOU SKIP THE WHOLE CHASE,
JUST GET IN THE CAR?

20:10.940 --> 20:13.272
IT'S LIKE THAT?

20:13.310 --> 20:15.574
I WANT YOU
TO TURN AROUND.

20:15.610 --> 20:18.704
TURN AROUND.
HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK.

20:18.750 --> 20:21.310
WELL,
THIS IS GOING NOWHERE.

20:21.350 --> 20:24.080
WE SHOULD TALK
TO HIS SPONSOR.

20:24.120 --> 20:26.509
YEAH, OKAY.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

20:26.550 --> 20:28.188
LET'S SPLIT UP.
I'LL TALK TO THE SPONSOR.

20:28.220 --> 20:29.881
YOU CALL TRACI,
FIND OUT WHERE THEY'RE AT.

20:29.920 --> 20:31.456
ALL RIGHT.

20:31.490 --> 20:33.549
AND I'LL LET THEM KNOW
WHERE WE'RE AT, WHICH IS,
ESSENTIALLY, NOWHERE.

20:33.600 --> 20:34.589
Gary:
DETECTIVE? YOU GOT A CALL.

20:34.630 --> 20:35.949
OH, OKAY.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.695
FIRST DOOR
ON THE RIGHT THERE.

20:41.040 --> 20:42.530
WELL,
SO HOW'S IT ALL GOING?

20:42.570 --> 20:45.539
WELL, YOU KNOW,
PRISONERS LOVE COPS.

20:45.570 --> 20:47.800
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHO DO YOU GOT LEFT?

20:47.840 --> 20:49.239
I HAVE NO IDEA.
I DON'T HAVE THE LIST.

20:49.280 --> 20:51.908
WELL,
LET'S CHECK MINE HERE.

20:51.950 --> 20:52.905
HERE WE GO.

20:52.950 --> 20:54.679
LOOKS LIKE
YOU'VE GOT THE GUY

20:54.720 --> 20:57.314
WHO DID LAUNDRY DETAIL
WITH LARRY, DEREK MOONEY,

20:57.350 --> 20:59.011
AND HIS SPONSOR,
JAY SWAREK.

20:59.050 --> 21:01.450
OH, SWAREK.
HE'S A REAL TALKY MAN.

21:01.490 --> 21:04.618
CAN I SEE THAT?
SURE.

21:04.660 --> 21:07.788
HEY.
WE GOT LARRY CHISHOLM.

21:07.830 --> 21:09.127
THEY'RE BRINGING HIM
INTO THE STATION NOW.

21:09.160 --> 21:10.661
LOOKS LIKE
WE CAN ROLL OUT OF HERE.

21:10.700 --> 21:12.463
THANK YOU.

21:12.500 --> 21:14.695
MY PLEASURE.

21:21.480 --> 21:23.038
I KNOW WHY
YOU WANT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

21:23.080 --> 21:24.968
YEAH.
RUSH-HOUR TRAFFIC.

21:25.010 --> 21:26.602
STOP.

21:26.650 --> 21:28.072
WHO WAS LARRY'S SPONSOR?

21:32.120 --> 21:34.315
UH...

21:35.990 --> 21:37.252
YOU DON'T WANT
TO MEET HIM.

21:37.290 --> 21:39.326
I'M NOT AFRAID
TO MEET HIM.

21:39.360 --> 21:43.399
HE HAS...NOTHING TO DO
WITH MY LIFE ANYMORE.

21:43.430 --> 21:44.522
BUT HE'S YOUR FATHER.

21:44.570 --> 21:46.128
SO?
YOUR DAD'S A DRINKER.

21:46.170 --> 21:48.035
YOU DON'T TELL ME
THOSE STORIES.

21:48.070 --> 21:49.537
WHAT STORIES?

21:49.570 --> 21:51.299
LITTLE MCNALLY
COMING HOME FROM SCHOOL,

21:51.340 --> 21:53.160
"MY DAD SAYS
HE'S NOT GONNA DRINK ANYMORE.

21:53.210 --> 21:55.633
HE PROMISED ME HE WOULDN'T
PASS OUT ON THE COUCH ANYMORE."

21:55.680 --> 21:57.477
CUT TO YOU
TRYING TO GET HIS SHOES OFF

21:57.510 --> 22:00.172
WHILE HE'S ON THE COUCH,
SWEARING AT YOU.

22:00.210 --> 22:02.349
I TOLD YOU EVERYTHING
ABOUT MY LIFE.

22:02.380 --> 22:04.439
WELL --
EVERYTHING.

22:04.490 --> 22:06.742
YEAH, WHY DO WE HAVE TO TALK
ABOUT ALL THAT STUFF?

22:06.790 --> 22:08.519
BECAUSE I WANT
TO KNOW YOU!

22:11.090 --> 22:14.389
THIS HAPPENS EVERY TIME!

22:14.430 --> 22:15.852
EVERYTHING'S GOING GREAT,

22:15.900 --> 22:18.323
AND THEN LIFE HAPPENS,
AND YOU SHUT DOWN.

22:18.370 --> 22:20.065
YEAH, AND THEN YOU GO UNDERCOVER
FOR SIX MONTHS.

22:20.100 --> 22:22.330
OH, MY GOD.
YOU BROKE UP WITH ME, SAM.

22:22.370 --> 22:24.235
OKAY?
WE WEREN'T EVEN TOGETHER.

22:24.270 --> 22:25.669
JERRY DIED!

22:25.710 --> 22:28.679
AND YOU LEFT.

22:36.020 --> 22:39.012
SAM, I AM NOT GOING IN
FOR ANOTHER ROUND OF THIS.

22:40.660 --> 22:41.809
I WON'T DO IT.

23:07.980 --> 23:11.108
[ SIGHS ]

23:11.150 --> 23:13.414
Gail:
SO, BRIAN GOWDY, HUH?

23:13.460 --> 23:15.587
WE STILL CAN'T FIGURE OUT
HOW YOU EVEN KNEW HIM.

23:15.620 --> 23:17.383
YOU DIDN'T VOLUNTEER
AT HIS CHARITIES,

23:17.430 --> 23:18.886
AND HE
DIDN'T DO TIME WITH YOU.

23:18.930 --> 23:20.079
I DON'T KNOW BRIAN GOWDY.

23:20.130 --> 23:22.325
WELL, THAT'S NOT WHAT YOUR
B.F.F. SEAN HARRISON SAID.

23:25.030 --> 23:26.463
SEAN TOLD YOU WHAT?

23:26.500 --> 23:28.764
THAT HE LENT YOU HIS CAR
THE DAY GOWDY WAS KILLED.

23:28.800 --> 23:31.030
HE TRIED TO GET IN TOUCH
WITH YOU, BUT YOU, UH --

23:31.070 --> 23:32.833
YOU WERE REALLY HARD
TO GET AHOLD OF.

23:32.870 --> 23:35.873
HE -- HE DIDN'T SAY THAT.

23:35.910 --> 23:39.038
HE'S IN WITH A DETECTIVE
RIGHT NOW.

23:39.080 --> 23:41.719
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

23:41.750 --> 23:44.981
ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS 1519.

23:45.020 --> 23:46.089
WE'RE JUST PULLING IN
WITH LARRY NOW.

23:46.120 --> 23:47.417
WE'LL BRING HIM THROUGH BOOKING
IN A MINUTE.

23:47.460 --> 23:49.314
[GRUNTING ]
DISPATCHER: Copy, 1519.

23:49.360 --> 23:52.557
HEY.
HEY, EASY, BUDDY. EASY.

23:52.590 --> 23:53.386
HEY'
HEY!

23:53.430 --> 23:54.920
UNH!

23:54.960 --> 23:57.622
WHOA! WHOA!
WHOA! WHOA!

23:57.670 --> 23:59.126
WE'RE IN THE SALLY PORT.
[ ALARMS BLARING ]

23:59.170 --> 24:01.991
SUSPECT HAS CUT HIS THROAT.
WE NEED MEDICS NOW.

24:02.040 --> 24:03.769
DISPATCHER: Okay.
Medics are on their way.

24:03.810 --> 24:05.209
OKAY, LARRY,
JUST BREATHE, OKAY?

24:05.240 --> 24:06.468
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

24:06.510 --> 24:07.807
YOUR EYES.
YOUR EYES, LARRY.

24:07.840 --> 24:09.432
OKAY, LARRY, LARRY,
LOOK AT ME!

24:13.110 --> 24:15.112
WHAT WAS THAT ALARM ABOUT?
IS SOMETHING HAPPENING?

24:15.150 --> 24:17.141
WE FOUND YOUR FRIEND,
LARRY CHISHOLM.

24:17.180 --> 24:19.045
DID HE SAY WNHéAT HAPPENED?

24:19.090 --> 24:21.308
BEFORE WE COULD BRING HIM IN
FOR QUESTIONING,

24:21.360 --> 24:22.759
HE TRIED
TO KILL HIMSELF.

24:22.790 --> 24:23.927
I NEED TO SEE HIM.

24:23.960 --> 24:26.383
SEAN, YOU CAN'T TALK TO HIM
UNTIL WE DO,

24:26.430 --> 24:28.421
AND WHEN WE DO,
IF HE SURVIVES,

24:28.460 --> 24:31.099
WE'RE CHARGING HIM
WITH FIRST-DEGREE MURDER.

24:31.130 --> 24:32.563
OH, MY GOD.

24:32.600 --> 24:35.091
LOOK, WE'RE GONNA SEND YOU TWO
HOME, BUT WE'LL CALL YOU.

24:35.140 --> 24:36.869
WE'LL FILL YOU IN ON LARRY'S
CONDITION WHEN WE KNOW ANYTHING.

24:36.900 --> 24:39.630
CH RIS?
YEAH.

24:39.670 --> 24:42.070
CAN YOU, UH, FILL OUT
THE PAPERWORK ON MR. HARRISON?

24:42.110 --> 24:43.236
SURE.

24:43.280 --> 24:46.602
RIGHT THIS WAY.

24:48.050 --> 24:49.813
THEY'RE GONNA BE
A FEW MINUTES.

24:49.850 --> 24:51.681
DID YOU WANT
TO GET SOME COFFEE?

24:51.720 --> 24:53.381
THAT'D BE GREAT.

24:53.420 --> 24:55.388
OKAY. THIS WAY.

24:55.420 --> 24:57.729
ASSAU LTING
A POLICE OFFICER.

24:57.760 --> 25:00.285
THAT WAS CHRISTMAS.

25:00.330 --> 25:03.766
THE NEIGHBORS CALLED IN
ANOTHER DOMESTIC.

25:03.800 --> 25:06.564
I TOLD THE POLICE
MY MOTHER FELL

25:06.600 --> 25:08.488
WHILE SHE WAS DECORATING
THE CHRISTMAS TREE.

25:10.070 --> 25:12.061
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

25:14.610 --> 25:15.975
UH, IT'S TRACI.

25:16.010 --> 25:17.375
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

25:17.410 --> 25:21.073
LARRY CHISHOLM IS IN THE
HOSPITAL IN CRITICAL CONDITION.

25:21.120 --> 25:24.578
HE TRIED
TO KILL HIMSELF.

25:24.620 --> 25:25.712
OH.

25:25.750 --> 25:27.047
DOES THAT
REALLY SOUND LIKE

25:27.090 --> 25:28.910
THE GUY
WE'VE BEEN HEARING ABOUT TODAY?

25:28.960 --> 25:31.224
HE GETS OUT, REPAYS
A PRISON DEBT BY KILLING GOWDY,

25:31.260 --> 25:32.329
THEN TRIES
TO KILL HIMSELF?

25:32.360 --> 25:33.588
DOES THAT MAKE SENSE?

25:33.630 --> 25:35.655
WELL, WE DON'T ACTUALLY KNOW
THAT HE WAS REPAYING A DEBT.

25:35.700 --> 25:38.919
SO, WE GOT A MURDER
AND A SUICIDE ATTEMPT

25:38.970 --> 25:40.665
WITH NO CLEAR MOTIVE.

25:42.540 --> 25:44.929
THERE IS SOMEONE
WE COULD TALK TO.

25:47.110 --> 25:48.407
YOU KNOW WHAT?

25:48.440 --> 25:49.907
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

25:49.940 --> 25:53.171
MCNALLY,
IT'S TIME YOU MET MY OLD MAN.

25:53.210 --> 25:55.417
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
THE COFFEE IN THE LOUNGE

25:55.450 --> 25:57.680
IS BETTER THAN THE COFFEE
IN THE SQUAD ROOM.

25:57.720 --> 26:00.382
WE HAVE VERY LOW
COFFEE STANDARDS AROUND HERE.

26:02.760 --> 26:04.250
OH, KELLY,
I'M SORRY.

26:04.290 --> 26:06.679
I THOUGHT
THEY PUT THAT AWAY ALREADY.

26:06.730 --> 26:08.049
THAT'S THE MAN
THAT WAS BEATEN?

26:08.100 --> 26:09.192
IT IS.

26:09.230 --> 26:11.061
HIS NAME'S BRIAN GOWDY.

26:11.100 --> 26:13.159
HE WAS A SCHOOLTEACHER.

26:13.200 --> 26:15.395
DO YOU RECOGNIZE HIM?

26:15.440 --> 26:18.261
NO.
I DON'T THINK SO.

26:18.310 --> 26:19.538
PAPERWORK'S IN ORDER.

26:19.570 --> 26:22.368
YOUR HUSBAND WILL BE AT
THE FRONT DESK IN A FEW MINUTES.

26:22.410 --> 26:24.105
DO YOU NEED A RIDE?

26:24.150 --> 26:25.447
NO, I DROVE.

26:29.950 --> 26:31.486
SHE SEEMED
KIND OF SPOOKED.

26:31.520 --> 26:32.987
I THINK
SHE JUST REALIZED

26:33.020 --> 26:35.614
WHAT THE MAN LIVING
IN HER BASEMENT IS CAPABLE OF.

26:41.800 --> 26:46.066
[ BUZZER ]

26:46.100 --> 26:47.636
THAN KS, BUD.

26:47.670 --> 26:49.968
HEARD YOU WERE HERE.

26:50.000 --> 26:53.606
I DIDN'T REALLY THINK
YOU'D HAVE THE STONES

26:53.640 --> 26:55.574
TO ACTUALLY COME AND SEE ME,
THOUGH.

26:55.610 --> 26:57.430
BUT THEN I SEE
YOU BROUGHT BACKUP.

26:57.480 --> 26:58.845
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

27:00.920 --> 27:03.684
THIS IS
OFFICER ANDY MCNALLY.

27:03.720 --> 27:05.938
AN DY?

27:05.990 --> 27:07.810
GOD, I WISH
I'D KNOWN YOU WERE COMING.

27:07.860 --> 27:09.953
I WOULD'VE THROWN ON SOMETHING
A LITTLE MORE WELCOMING.

27:09.990 --> 27:13.426
WE HAVE A FEW QUESTIONS
ABOUT LARRY CHISHOLM.

27:13.460 --> 27:16.588
WHO?
THE MAN YOU WERE SPONSORING
IN ADDICTION RECOVERY.

27:16.630 --> 27:18.518
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU'RE DEALING
WITH YOUR DEMONS, DAD.

27:18.570 --> 27:20.765
LOOKS GOOD ON A PAROLE
APPLICATION. I'M UP
FOR EARLY RELEASE.

27:20.800 --> 27:21.835
OH.

27:21.870 --> 27:24.930
HEY, DO THEY STILL
MAKE THOSE, UH...

27:24.970 --> 27:27.734
THOSE HOT TURKEY SANDWICHES
WITH ALL THE GRAW DOWN THERE

27:27.780 --> 27:29.975
AT THAT LITTLE HOLE IN THE WALL
IN WASHINGTON?

27:30.010 --> 27:32.478
I DON'T KNOW, POP.

27:32.510 --> 27:34.478
USED TO TAKE HIM THERE
SUNDAYS.

27:34.520 --> 27:36.738
WE HAD A LITTLE MAN TIME,
HIM AND ME.

27:36.780 --> 27:37.917
ALWAYS WENT THERE,

27:37.950 --> 27:40.817
BECAUSE SOMETIMES HIS MOTHER
COULD BE A LITTLE...

27:43.830 --> 27:45.457
HOW IS
YOUR LOONEY MOTHER?

27:45.490 --> 27:49.324
MY MOTHER'S GOOD.
SHE'S SOMEWHERE WARM.

27:49.360 --> 27:50.657
OH.

27:50.700 --> 27:53.021
AND I DIDN'T
KEEP THE HOUSE WARM?

27:53.070 --> 27:54.367
I DON'T THINK THAT'S WHAT
I SAID. IS THAT WHAT I SAID?

27:54.400 --> 27:55.469
I WORKED.

27:55.500 --> 27:58.606
SOMETIMES THINGS WOULD GO
A LITTLE WRONG.

27:58.640 --> 28:01.279
ANDY HERE KNOWS
HOW THAT GOES.

28:01.310 --> 28:04.905
ANYWAY, WHO NEEDS THAT...
MOTHER OF YOURS, ANWVAY?

28:04.950 --> 28:09.068
I GOT THIS SWEET LITTLE THING
THAT COMES IN HERE TO SEE ME.

28:09.120 --> 28:13.238
VERY SWEET.
THAT'D BE YOUR CONJUGAL STEPMOM.

28:13.290 --> 28:14.211
YOU KNOW WHAT?

28:14.260 --> 28:16.251
YOU SHOULD ASK
OFFICER ANDY OVER HERE

28:16.290 --> 28:17.723
IF SHE'D LIKE
TO COME ALONG ONE TIME

28:17.760 --> 28:19.580
AND SHE CAN MEET
YOUR CONJUGAL STEPMOM.

28:19.630 --> 28:21.222
WOULDN'T THAT BE NICE?

28:21.260 --> 28:23.194
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

28:23.230 --> 28:25.118
DON'T TRY AND TELL ME

28:25.170 --> 28:28.833
THAT YOU'VE NEVER TRIED IT ON
WITH, UH...

28:28.870 --> 28:31.065
LARRY CHISHOLM --
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT HIM?

28:31.110 --> 28:34.170
YOU KNOW, IF I GOT A CHANCE
TO WORK WITH THAT EVERY DAY...

28:34.210 --> 28:35.905
EXCUSE ME.

28:35.940 --> 28:38.408
UH, OFFICER ANDY, I KNOW
YOU LIKE TO ASK THE QUESTIONS.

28:38.450 --> 28:40.099
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

28:40.150 --> 28:41.742
HAS MY SON EVER TOLD YOU

28:41.780 --> 28:45.546
THE STORY ABOUT HOW IT IS
THAT I ENDED UP IN JAIL?

28:47.760 --> 28:51.753
NO. NO? WHAT,
NOT INTERESTING ENOUGH?

28:51.790 --> 28:53.326
LARRY CHISHOLM --
DID HE HAVE ANY DEBTS

28:53.360 --> 28:54.759
HE HAD TO PAY OFF
WHEN HE GOT OUT?

28:54.800 --> 28:56.153
YOU KNOW,
ALL I WANTED TO HEAR

28:56.200 --> 29:01.399
ALL THESE YEARS
IS JUST FOR YOU TO ADMIT IT.

29:01.440 --> 29:04.238
JUST SAY IT.
BUT NO.

29:04.270 --> 29:07.876
ISN'T IT SAD THAT A MAN
HAS TO HIDE BEHIND A BADGE

29:07.910 --> 29:10.401
JUST TO STAND UP
TO HIS OLD MAN?

29:10.440 --> 29:12.670
YOU'RE PROBABLY AFRAID
THAT THEY MIGHT STEAL

29:12.710 --> 29:14.814
YOUR PRECIOUS BADGE
AWAY FROM YOU, RIGHT?

29:14.850 --> 29:16.044
JUST TAKE IT BACK.

29:16.080 --> 29:18.810
AND I'M TELLING YOU RIGHT NOW,
THEY WOULD.

29:18.850 --> 29:21.853
IF THEY KNEW THE STORY,
IF SOMEONE WERE TO TELL THEM,

29:21.890 --> 29:23.209
THEY'D TAKE YOUR BADGE.

29:23.260 --> 29:25.285
THAT'S IT.
TIME TO GO.

29:25.330 --> 29:28.959
JUST HOPE THAT WOMAN'S
NOT IN TOO MUCH DANGER.

29:29.000 --> 29:30.592
[ BUZZER ]
SAM.

29:33.630 --> 29:35.063
JUST GIVE ME FIVE MINUTES.

29:38.310 --> 29:40.801
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'VE GOT IT.

29:52.650 --> 29:55.210
SO, JUST TELL ME --
ARE YOU AND SAMMY A COUPLE?

29:56.560 --> 30:00.155
WELL, WATCH OUT.
THAT'S ALLS I CAN SAY.

30:00.190 --> 30:03.398
YOU WERE
LARRY'S SPONSOR.

30:03.430 --> 30:05.318
HE MUST'VE BEEN LIKE A SON
TO YOU.

30:05.370 --> 30:06.667
YEAH.
ACTUALLY, YEAH.

30:06.700 --> 30:09.965
MORE OF A SON TO ME
THAN SAM EVER WAS.

30:10.000 --> 30:11.706
LARRY CALLED YOU AFTER BRIAN
GOWDY WAS KILLED, DIDN'T HE?

30:14.740 --> 30:16.970
'COURSE. YEAH.

30:17.010 --> 30:19.171
HE CALLED ME.

30:21.850 --> 30:23.477
TELLING ME
THAT HIS PSYCHOPATHIC BUDDY

30:23.520 --> 30:24.885
WAS STARTING
TO PUSH HIM AGAIN.

30:24.920 --> 30:25.887
YOU MEAN SEAN HARRISON.

30:25.920 --> 30:27.182
THEY GREW UP
IN A GROUP HOME TOGETHER.

30:27.220 --> 30:28.414
AND WHEN THEY WERE KIDS,

30:28.460 --> 30:30.280
THIS GUY
REALLY HAD LARRY'S BACK.

30:30.320 --> 30:31.958
NOW HE OWNS HIS BALLS.

30:31.990 --> 30:35.153
LARRY HAS THE BRAIN
OF A SPRING LAMB, OKAY?

30:35.200 --> 30:36.690
BUT HE'S A GOOD GUY.

30:36.730 --> 30:38.322
WELL, DID HE SAY WHY HARRISON
WAS PUSHING HIM AROUND?

30:38.370 --> 30:40.964
YEAH.

30:41.000 --> 30:43.195
ARE YOU AND SAMMY
A COUPLE?

30:43.240 --> 30:46.334
I CARE ABOUT SAM.

30:46.370 --> 30:48.474
VERY MUCH.

30:48.510 --> 30:50.774
OKAY.

30:54.280 --> 30:56.043
HARRISON WAS FOLLOWING
HIS WIFE AROUND.

30:56.080 --> 30:59.083
HE FOLLOWS HER TO A MOTEL,
HE SEES HER GO IN THERE,

30:59.120 --> 31:01.350
SO OBVIOUSLY, SHE'S GETTING
BONED ON THE SIDE BY SOME GUY,

31:01.390 --> 31:03.153
SO HE WAITS OUTSIDE,
WATCHES THE GUY COME OUT,

31:03.190 --> 31:05.124
DOESN'T RECOGNIZE HIM,
BUT HE CLIMBS INTO THIS CAR,

31:05.160 --> 31:08.391
THIS BLACK CAR
THAT'S GOT A RIDE SWAPPER.

31:08.430 --> 31:10.352
SO NOW
HE'S MAKING LARRY

31:10.400 --> 31:14.268
TEST-DRIVE EVERY MATCHING CAR
ON THE SITE.

31:14.300 --> 31:17.269
AND THEN LARRY SAYS,
YOU KNOW,

31:17.300 --> 31:19.234
"WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW FOR
AND EVERYTHING?"

31:19.270 --> 31:21.431
AND HE SAYS, WELL, THAT
HE'S NOT GONNA HURT THE GUY.

31:21.480 --> 31:22.777
HE'S JUST
GONNA TALK TO HIM.

31:22.810 --> 31:26.143
SO LARRY MADE ALL THE CALLS
AND DID ALL THE TEST-DRIVES.

31:26.180 --> 31:29.274
HE BROUGHT BRIAN GOWDY
TO SEAN HARRISON, DIDN'T HE?

31:29.320 --> 31:31.641
YEP. YOU GOT IT.

31:31.690 --> 31:33.419
OKAY, AND HARRISON
BEAT BRIAN GOWDY TO DEATH.

31:33.450 --> 31:35.589
LARRY HAD ABSOLUTELY NOTHING
TO DO WITH THAT.

31:35.620 --> 31:37.508
YOU GOT TO TRUST ME
ON THAT ONE, OKAY?

31:37.560 --> 31:39.551
ALL LARRY WANTED
WAS JUST TO GET SOBER

31:39.590 --> 31:41.649
AND WANTED
TO GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

31:41.700 --> 31:44.021
AND THEN THIS HARRISON GUY
STARTS RANTING

31:44.070 --> 31:46.561
ABOUT HOW HE'S GONNA DO THE WIFE
MAYBE, TOO,

31:46.600 --> 31:48.363
SO LARRY'S GOT TO GET --
JUST GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

31:48.400 --> 31:49.560
WHY DIDN'T HE
JUST CALL THE POLICE?

31:49.600 --> 31:51.136
OH, COME ON.
DON'T BE STUPID.

31:51.170 --> 31:53.058
HE'S GONNA END UP
RIGHT BACK IN HERE.

31:54.640 --> 31:56.676
THANK YOU.

31:59.750 --> 32:01.718
HEY, WAIT.

32:01.750 --> 32:05.015
JUST TELL ME THIS.

32:05.050 --> 32:07.189
WHAT DID SAMMY TELL YOU
ABOUT ME?

32:08.690 --> 32:09.952
[ BUZZER ]

32:09.990 --> 32:11.651
FIRST I'VE HEARD
OF YOU.

32:15.830 --> 32:17.024
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

32:17.060 --> 32:18.766
DETECTIVE,
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

32:18.800 --> 32:20.688
SEAN HARRISON
KILLED BRIAN GOWDY.

32:20.730 --> 32:22.789
KELLY WAS HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH HIM.

32:22.840 --> 32:23.864
WHERE'S KELLY NOW?

32:23.900 --> 32:25.231
WITH SEAN.
LET'S GO.

32:40.020 --> 32:42.011
Peck, Peck.
Go around that side.

32:42.060 --> 32:45.120
Right there. Let's go.

32:53.500 --> 32:55.434
SEAN HARRISON!

32:57.270 --> 32:58.635
THIS IS THE POLICE!

32:58.670 --> 33:00.604
WE ARE INSIDE THE HOUSE!

33:10.020 --> 33:12.011
[ SCRUBBING ]

33:16.520 --> 33:19.318
NICK.

33:19.360 --> 33:21.248
KELLY?

33:21.300 --> 33:23.689
YEAH. HI.

33:23.730 --> 33:25.664
KELLY, WHAT HAPPENED?

33:25.700 --> 33:29.898
NOTHING.
YOU KNOW, THE USUAL.

33:29.940 --> 33:32.033
NOTHING.

33:32.070 --> 33:34.106
IT'S NOT EVEN OUR PLACE,
YOU KNOW.

33:34.140 --> 33:35.300
IT'S A RENTAL.

33:35.340 --> 33:36.375
KELLY, I'M JUST
GONNA GRAB THE KNIFE.

33:36.410 --> 33:37.638
NO, NO, NO, NO!
IT'S GROSS.

33:37.680 --> 33:39.739
I NEED
TO CLEAN IT OFF.

33:39.780 --> 33:41.714
BRIAN GOWDY --
YOU KNEW HIM?

33:41.750 --> 33:43.377
SEAN KILLED HIM.

33:43.420 --> 33:46.048
I DIDN'T KNOW.

33:46.090 --> 33:49.389
I DIDN'T KNOW
UNTIL I SAW THE PICTURES.

33:49.420 --> 33:52.321
FOR A SECOND,
I THOUGHT, MAYBE...

33:52.360 --> 33:54.897
I'D MISSED
PART OF THE PLAN.

33:54.930 --> 33:56.124
BRIAN'S SO SMART.

33:56.160 --> 33:59.323
I THOUGHT MAYBE --
MAYBE I MISSED PART OF THE PLAN.

33:59.370 --> 34:00.564
TO DISAPPEAR
TO COSTA RICA?

34:00.600 --> 34:02.659
OKAY.

34:02.700 --> 34:04.702
YOU GUYS LEFT ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.
WHAT HAPPENED?

34:08.780 --> 34:12.477
SEAN MADE ME
GET IN THE CAR.

34:12.510 --> 34:15.308
HE KNEW I KNEW.

34:15.350 --> 34:19.548
HE STARTED PUNCHING ME
IN THE CAR.

34:19.590 --> 34:24.220
I JUST CURLED UP...
AND CLOSED MY EYES.

34:24.260 --> 34:28.128
IT'S SO WEIRD.

34:28.160 --> 34:30.799
WE GOT BACK HERE, AND SEAN
WAS JUST GOING OFF ON ME,

34:30.830 --> 34:33.390
AND ALL I COULD SEE
WAS THIS KNIFE.

34:33.430 --> 34:35.739
IT WAS LIKE BRIAN
PUT IT THERE.

34:35.770 --> 34:38.159
I KNOW
THAT'S CRAZY, BUT...

34:38.210 --> 34:42.977
OH, MY GOD.

34:43.010 --> 34:44.272
[ KNIFE CLATTERS ]

34:44.310 --> 34:45.777
[ Crying ] OH, MY GOD.

34:57.860 --> 34:59.851
[ BUZZER ]

35:02.930 --> 35:05.228
SO, SUDDENLY,
YOU CAN'T GET ENOUGH OF ME?

35:05.270 --> 35:07.795
OKAY. GO AHEAD.

35:07.830 --> 35:09.536
GET IT OFF YOUR CHEST.

35:09.570 --> 35:10.832
YEAH.
COME ON. LET'S GO.

35:10.870 --> 35:14.306
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE KID,
I REMEMBER -- I REMEMBER, UH,

35:14.340 --> 35:16.900
WAKING UP
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,

35:16.940 --> 35:19.602
GOT TO GET A GLASS OF WATER,
AND, UH...

35:19.650 --> 35:22.869
I DIDN'T KNOW IF
I WAS IN FOR A SMACK IN THE HEAD

35:22.920 --> 35:24.649
OR A -- AN HOUR-LONG,
HOT-WHISKEY-BREATH LECTURE

35:24.690 --> 35:25.987
ON THE CIVIL WAR --

35:26.020 --> 35:27.715
YOU DON'T THINK I WANTED
TO BEAT MY OLD MAN UP EVERY DAY?

35:27.750 --> 35:29.650
YOU DON'T THINK I WANTED
TO PUNCH HIS TEETH OUT?

35:29.690 --> 35:31.851
I WAS SO SCARED OF YOU.

35:31.890 --> 35:34.620
AND THEN,
I WAS ANGRY WITH YOU,

35:34.660 --> 35:37.549
AND --
AND THEN, FOR A LONG TIME,

35:37.600 --> 35:39.693
I WAS WORRIED I'D BE LIKE YOU,
YOU KNOW?

35:39.730 --> 35:42.528
OH, YEAH.
YEAH.

35:42.570 --> 35:44.162
BUT HERE WE ARE,
AND, UH...

35:44.210 --> 35:46.201
YEAH, HERE WE ARE.

35:46.240 --> 35:49.835
SITTING HERE, LOOKING AT YOU,
AND I SEE YOUR, UH...

35:49.880 --> 35:54.670
SAD, ANGRY OLD FACE,
AND I REALIZE...

35:54.720 --> 35:56.472
I'M FREE.

35:56.520 --> 36:00.149
AND I'M NOT GONNA WASTE
ONE MORE EMOTION ON YOU.

36:00.190 --> 36:02.556
WHAT IS THIS?
YOUR "I FORGIVE YOU" SPEECH?

36:02.590 --> 36:05.058
IT'S PRETTY LAME.
JUST LISTEN TO ME, OKAY?

36:05.090 --> 36:06.819
I DO NOT FORGIVE YOU.

36:06.860 --> 36:07.929
YOU DON'T HAVE TO,

36:07.960 --> 36:10.326
'CAUSE I NEVER FELT GUILTY
FOR ONE SECOND.

36:13.900 --> 36:16.789
YOU DESERVED
EVERYTHING YOU GOT FROM ME.

36:16.840 --> 36:18.762
DO YOU HEAR ME
ON THAT?

36:20.340 --> 36:22.171
I FORGIVE YOU, POP.

36:24.910 --> 36:26.707
HOW SWEET. JUST GET
THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

36:26.750 --> 36:28.741
[ BUZZER ]

36:30.420 --> 36:32.240
[ SIREN WAILS ]

36:32.290 --> 36:35.509
KELLY GETTING SECOND-DEGREE,
IT JUST DOESN'T SEEM RIGHT.

36:35.560 --> 36:38.484
WELL, HER LAWYER'S JUST
GONNA ARGUE SELF-DEFENSE.

36:38.530 --> 36:39.656
I'M OKAY WITH THAT.

36:39.690 --> 36:42.693
ME, TOO.

36:43.860 --> 36:46.124
I'LL LEAVE YOU TO IT.

36:46.170 --> 36:48.559
DEX.
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

36:48.600 --> 36:51.603
NICE MOVE TODAY, SENDING
YOUR BOYFRIEND TO GET ME.

36:51.640 --> 36:52.959
I DON'T WANT
TO FIGHT WITH YOU.

36:53.010 --> 36:54.807
NO, IF YOU DIDN'T WANT TO FIGHT,
YOU WOULD'VE COME YOURSELF.

36:54.840 --> 36:55.977
I WAS WORKING.

36:56.010 --> 36:58.205
I'M BUSY,
LIKE I ALWAYS AM,

36:58.250 --> 36:59.706
WHICH IS YOUR BIG PROBLEM
WITH ME.

36:59.750 --> 37:01.877
LOOK, I WORK -- A LOT.

37:01.920 --> 37:05.014
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
I'M NOT A GOOD MOTHER.

37:05.050 --> 37:06.779
WHAT DOES IT MEAN,
THEN?

37:06.820 --> 37:09.880
WHEN YOU DIDN'T SHOW UP
TO MEDIATION THIS MORNING,

37:09.920 --> 37:10.955
I WAS GLAD.

37:10.990 --> 37:14.084
AND THEN I FOUND OUT
YOU WERE IN THE HOSPITAL.

37:14.130 --> 37:15.449
I'M FINE. OKAY?

37:15.500 --> 37:18.560
LOOK,
WE'RE NOT TOGETHER ANYMORE,

37:18.600 --> 37:23.139
BUT NO ONE ELSE WILL EVER
LOVE LEO LIKE YOU AND I DO.

37:23.170 --> 37:25.866
W-WE'VE GOT
THE SAME FAVORITE MEMORIES --

37:25.910 --> 37:30.335
YOU KNOW, ALL THE FIRSTS,
ALL THE FUNNY THINGS HE SAYS.

37:30.380 --> 37:34.100
SO YOU BETTER NOT
LET ANYTHING HAPPEN TO YOU,

37:34.150 --> 37:36.948
'CAUSE WHAT IF I FORGET?

37:36.980 --> 37:38.914
WHO'S GONNA REMIND ME?

37:58.540 --> 38:00.508
YOU KNOW I FOUGHT FOR YOU
AS HARD AS I COULD

38:00.540 --> 38:02.735
IN THE HOSPITAL,
RIGHT?

38:02.780 --> 38:04.008
I KNOW.

38:04.040 --> 38:06.179
AND THEY WOULDN'T EVEN
LET ME IN THE ROOM.

38:06.210 --> 38:08.144
DOV,
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

38:08.180 --> 38:09.943
REALLY,
I'M JUST MAD AT MYSELF.

38:09.980 --> 38:12.016
I MEAN, GOD,
I GET DRUNK OFF TEQUILA,

38:12.050 --> 38:14.484
MARRY SOME GUY
'CAUSE I THINK IT'S HYSTERICAL,

38:14.520 --> 38:15.919
AND THEN HE'S IN CHARGE

38:15.960 --> 38:18.053
OF MY MAJOR
LIFE-THREATENING SURGERIES.

38:18.090 --> 38:21.890
AND, LOOK,
IT IS NOT YOUR FAULT.

38:21.930 --> 38:23.921
I AM SO SORRY.

38:27.100 --> 38:28.431
FORGIVE AND FORGET?

38:31.100 --> 38:32.761
FORGIVE AND FORGET.

38:35.780 --> 38:37.577
WANT TO GET DRUNK
AND MAKE OUT?

38:37.610 --> 38:40.670
YES,
BUT NOT ON TEQUILA.

38:40.710 --> 38:42.211
OKAY.

38:46.150 --> 38:48.983
WE USED TO WATCH "MILLIONAIRE"
TOGETHER WHEN I WAS A KID.

38:49.020 --> 38:51.921
HE WAS IN AND OUT OF PRISON
ALL OUR LIVES,

38:51.960 --> 38:53.780
AS YOU KNOW,
BUT, UH...

38:53.830 --> 38:57.152
WHEN HE WAS OUT,
WE USED TO WATCH THAT GAME SHOW.

38:57.200 --> 38:59.668
YOU REMEMBER?
MM-HMM. I DO.

38:59.700 --> 39:01.895
IT WAS THE ONE THING WE HAD
IN COMMON WHEN I WAS GROWING UP.

39:01.940 --> 39:05.068
WE, UH, BOTH WANTED
TO BE MILLIONAIRES.

39:05.110 --> 39:08.978
I WANTED IT SO I COULD GET MY
MOTHER AND SISTER AWAY FROM HIM.

39:09.010 --> 39:12.173
I HAVE NO IDEA WHY
HE WANTED TO BE A MILLIONAIRE.

39:12.210 --> 39:16.909
DID HE TELL YOU WHY HE WENT
TO PRISON THE LAST TIME?

39:16.950 --> 39:18.383
NO.

39:18.420 --> 39:19.887
NO?

39:19.920 --> 39:23.811
THE COPS WANTED HIM
ON A ROBBERY/ASSAULT,

39:23.860 --> 39:26.055
BUT HE HAD AN ALIBI.

39:26.090 --> 39:29.992
HE SAID THAT
HE WAS AT HOME WITH HIS BOY,

39:30.030 --> 39:32.169
WATCHING "MILLIONAIRE."

39:32.200 --> 39:35.863
AND THEY ASKED ME ABOUT IT,
AND, UH...

39:35.900 --> 39:37.458
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:37.500 --> 39:40.708
I TOLD THEM
HE WAS LYING.

39:40.740 --> 39:43.903
AND...
HE GOT SIX MONTHS.

39:43.940 --> 39:49.116
WHEN HE WAS INSIDE,
GOT INTO A FIGHT, KILLED A GUY.

39:49.150 --> 39:50.310
20 YEARS.

39:50.350 --> 39:53.547
WAS HE
TELLING THE TRUTH?

39:53.590 --> 39:55.217
OR WERE YOU?

39:59.090 --> 40:00.250
HE WAS.

40:00.290 --> 40:03.418
MM.

40:10.100 --> 40:11.931
MORE THAN
YOU WANTED TO HEAR?

40:15.610 --> 40:16.929
NO.

40:23.450 --> 40:26.089
YOU ARE NOTHING LIKE
THAT MAN.

40:26.120 --> 40:28.418
AND IF YOU EVER DOUBT IT,

40:28.460 --> 40:30.883
YOU JUST NEED TO TURN AROUND
AND ASK ME.

40:30.920 --> 40:35.220
OH, YEAH?
YOU GONNA BE THERE?

40:35.260 --> 40:38.491
[ SCOFFS ] JUST TRY
AND GET RID OF ME.

40:38.530 --> 40:40.998
OKAY, WELL, THAT SOUNDED
A LITTLE BIT STALKERY.

40:41.030 --> 40:43.294
YOU DO HAVE SOME SAY.

40:43.340 --> 40:45.763
* I'M JUST A PIECE
OF LIGHT *

40:45.810 --> 40:48.005
I LOVE YOU, MCNALLY.

40:48.040 --> 40:51.498
* ON MY OWN

40:51.550 --> 40:54.246
I LOVE YOU,
SAM SWAREK.

40:54.280 --> 40:57.647
* CAN'T WAIT TO BE
YOURS TONIGHT *

40:57.680 --> 41:00.513
SO, UH,
WHERE TO NEXT?

41:00.550 --> 41:06.227
* KEEP ME WARM

41:06.260 --> 41:09.457
MCNALLY IS BRILLIANT.

41:09.500 --> 41:11.821
MM-HMM.

41:11.870 --> 41:14.088
MCNALLY IS BEAUTIFUL.

41:14.130 --> 41:19.659
MCNALLY IS ALWAYS FUN
TO BE WITH.

41:19.710 --> 41:21.507
HEY.

41:22.980 --> 41:26.108
WHICH ONE OF THOSE
IS THE LIE, HMM?

41:26.150 --> 41:29.176
WELL...
MAYBE I DON'T WANT TO LIE.

41:29.220 --> 41:30.915
OH, YEAH?
YEAH.

41:30.950 --> 41:32.417
REALLY?

41:32.450 --> 41:34.850
REALLY.

41:34.890 --> 41:37.916
THE TRUTH.

41:37.960 --> 41:41.999
I TOLD MCNALLY
THE WHOLE STORY TODAY.

41:42.030 --> 41:44.692
AND SHE'S STILL HERE.

41:49.700 --> 41:53.136
IN FACT,
SHE'S RIGHT HERE...

41:53.170 --> 41:56.003
* IS THERE A PLACE FOR ME?

41:56.040 --> 41:57.371
...TRYING TO SEDUCE ME.

41:57.410 --> 41:59.708
[ CHUCKLES ] TRYING?

41:59.750 --> 42:02.548
PLEASE, DETECTIVE.

42:02.580 --> 42:08.041
TRUTH -- MCNALLY MAKES ME
FEEL ALIVE.

42:08.090 --> 42:11.651
YOU ARE THE WORST
AT THIS GAME.

42:11.690 --> 42:12.952
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

42:12.990 --> 42:14.480
GOOD.
